	<!--Standard View of Tabs -->
				<div id="demo" class="yui-navset">
				    <ul class="yui-nav">
				        <li class="selected"><a href="#tab1"><em>WHY CHOOSE&nbsp;</em></a></li>
				        <li><a href="#tab2"><em>PHONE NUMBERS&nbsp;</em></a></li>

				    <div class="yui-content">
				        <div id="tab1">
				        	<div id="ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_ctl05__ControlWrapper_RichHtmlField" style="display:inline"><p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Headline>Legendary Roadside Assistance</span><br>24-hour Roadside Assistance is the reason why most of our members became members, and—for many—the reason they renew every year.</p>
<p>If you lock your keys in your car, get a flat tire, need a jump start, or are broken down at the side of the road, we can be there to help you on your way, day or night.<sup>1</sup></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a href="http://ww2.aaa.com/scripts/WebObjects.dll/AAAOnline?association=aaa&amp;club=252&amp;page=ERSHomePage">REQUEST ROAD SERVICE ONLINE</a></span></p>
<hr>
<a name=roadside></a>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Headline>Priority Service at a AAA Approved Auto Repair Facility</span><br>Members now receive Priority Service when towed by a AAA independent service provider to a AAA Approved Auto Repair facility. Priority Service includes prompt vehicle evaluation within 60 minutes of AAA tow arrival, assistance in obtaining alternate transportation, and a 10 percent discount on regularly–priced parts and labor, up to $50.<sup>2</sup></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a href="/en-tx/buy-maintain-vehicles/vehicle-maintenance/pages/aarhome.aspx">FIND THE NEAREST AAA APPROVED AUTO REPAIR FACILITY</a></span></p>
<hr>
<a name=batteryservice></a>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Headline>Battery testing and replacement that comes to you</span><br>If you have a failed battery, AAA Battery Service provides a convenient mobile battery testing and replacement service to get you back on the road. If your battery fails the test and needs replacing, the technician will offer you a professionally installed AAA battery at a discounted price for AAA members.<sup>3</sup></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a href="/en-tx/driving-resources/get-roadside-assistance/Pages/aaa-battery-service.aspx">BATTERY REPLACEMENT</a></span></p>
<hr>
<a name=findme></a>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Headline>Location assistance with AAA FindMe</span><br>AAA has teamed up with Sprint and AT&amp;T to provide you with AAA FindMe, enabling AAA to automatically receive your geographic location when you call for AAA Roadside Assistance from a Sprint or AT&amp;T wireless phone.<sup>4</sup><br><br>AAA FindMe benefits include:</p>
<ul class=stp>
<li>Identifying your location, even when you are in<br>an unfamiliar area</li>
<li>Providing freedom from worry, knowing thatAAA can<br>locate you quickly</li>
<li>Available at no additional fee<sup>5</sup></li></ul>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a title="" href="/_layouts/acsc/link/authalp.aspx?tid=AAAFindMe" target="_blank">REGISTER FOR AAA FINDME</a></span></p>
<hr>
<a name=mobileapp></a>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Headline>AAA Mobile App</span><br>With the AAA Mobile app, you can now access Roadside Assistance, member discounts, maps, gas prices, driving directions, and other information all from one integrated app.</p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a title="" href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/aaa-discounts/id310730297?mt=8" target="_blank">DOWNLOAD FOR iPHONE</a></span> | <span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a title="" href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.aaa.android.discounts&amp;feature=more_from_developer#?t=W10" target="_blank">DOWNLOAD FOR ANDROID</a></span></p>
<hr>
<a name=onboard></a>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Headline>AAA OnBoard<sup>®</sup></span><br>When you sign up for the AAA OnBoard<sup>®</sup> Insurance Program, AAA can locate your vehicle for roadside assistance and gather remote diagnostics which may assist us in diagnosing problems before our independent service providers arrive.<sup>6</sup></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Highlight><a title="" href="/en-tx/get-insurance/Pages/OnBoard.aspx">LEARN MORE</a></span></p>
<hr>

<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Small-Type><sup>1</sup>As a member you may call for help as many times as you need it. Every membership year, you and all the other members of your family who join AAA are allowed up to four free calls for Roadside Assistance each. After that, a service charge applies. Free towing up to three miles from the point of breakdown or unlimited miles back to the service facility providing the service. Service is generally provided by independent service providers and is limited to the US and Canada. Certain conditions and limitations apply. See the Member Guide for more information.</span></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Small-Type><sup>2</sup>Upon request, members save 10% (up to $50) on regularly-priced parts and labor at participating AAA Show Your Card &amp; Save® Approved Auto Repair facilities. Cannot be combined with any other discount or coupon. Valid AAA membership card must be presented at a participating AAA Approved Auto Repair facility at time of service. </p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Small-Type><sup>3</sup><strong>AAA Battery Service is generally provided by independent service providers and is only available in select areas during select hours.</strong> The diagnostics test is free during your four free Roadside Assistance calls per membership year. AAA batteries are available for most vehicle makes and models. Copies of the warranties are available for inspection from the technician at any time upon request. Membership Roadside Assistance terms and conditions apply. See the Member Guide brochure for details.</span></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Small-Type><sup>4</sup>GPS-enabled handsets only. Members must have a Sprint or AT&amp;T GPS-enabled handset and provide permission to release location information to AAA in advance of the roadside assistance call.</span></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Small-Type><sup>5</sup>Roadside assistance requires AAA membership, available separately.</span></p>
<p><span class=ms-rteCustom-Small-Type><sup>6</sup>The AAA OnBoard<sup>®</sup> Program is available to Auto Club members who agree to the Program's Terms of Use and are insured by Interinsurance Exchange of the Automobile Club. AAA OnBoard<sup>®</sup> services depend on wireless and GPS coverage, and require a compatible vehicle type (excluding 1995 or older, hybrid and electric vehicles). Certain restrictions and limits apply. If the device collects sufficient mileage information, this will be used to determine your annual mileage at renewal. Diagnostic codes are not available for all vehicles and in all circumstances.</span></p></span></span></div>
